Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-gen-z-travel-debt-affirm-klarna-credit-cards-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20desire%20to%20see%20the%20world%3C%2Fa%3E%20broke%20his%20discipline.%20%26quot%3BI%20built%20up%20points%20to%20travel%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BBut%20when%20I%20travel%2C%20I%20want%20to%20go%20shopping%2C%20and%20that's%20where%20the%20spending%20gets%20out%20of%20control.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20three%20years%2C%20Danikowski%20has%20racked%20up%20about%20%2415%2C000%20in%20debt%20across%20three%20cards%2C%20one%20of%20which%20has%20an%20interest%20rate%20of%2028%25.%20He%20makes%20his%20minimum%20payments%20each%20month%20%E2%80%94%20a%20task%20that%20has%20become%20much%20harder%20since%20he%20lost%20his%20job%20this%20year%20%E2%80%94%20and%20tries%20to%20resist%20the%20urge%20to%20keep%20using%20the%20cards%2C%20but%20his%20balance%20doesn't%20budge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20everyday%20things%2C%20I%20choose%20comfort%20over%20everything%20else%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDanikowski%20and%20many%20other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcredit-card-debt-crisis-subprime-credit-scores-millennials-gen-z-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Zers%20are%20rapidly%20building%20up%20credit-card%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20TransUnion%20study%20found%20that%2C%20adjusting%20for%20inflation%2C%20the%20average%20credit-card%20balance%20for%20someone%20who%20was%2022%20to%2024%20at%20the%20end%20of%20last%20year%20was%20%242%2C834%2C%20a%2026%25%20increase%20from%20the%20average%20figure%20for%20millennials%20who%20were%20the%20same%20age%20a%20decade%20ago.%20The%20study%20also%20suggested%20that%20Gen%20Zers%20were%20much%20more%20comfortable%20with%20credit%20cards%20than%20prior%20generations%20were%3A%20They%20were%20opening%20more%20cards%2C%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20fall%20behind%20on%20payments%2C%20and%20were%20using%20the%20cards%20for%20more%20types%20of%20purchases.%20Alev%20told%20me%20Credit%20Karma%20data%20shows%20Gen%20Zers%20are%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcredit-card-debt-crisis-subprime-credit-scores-millennials-gen-z-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20acquiring%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20faster%20rate%20than%20any%20other%20age%20group.%20The%20combination%20of%20an%20increasingly%20turbulent%20economy%20and%20Gen%20Zers'%20desire%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgenz-millennials-going-into-debt-summer-vacation-travel-taylor-swift-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emake%20up%20for%20lost%20time%3C%2Fa%3E%20via%20pandemic%20%26quot%3Brevenge%20spending%26quot%3B%20has%20left%20many%20members%20of%20the%20generation%20overly%20reliant%20on%20credit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGen%20Z%20really%20prioritizes%20fun%20over%20finances%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20things%20like%20eating%20out%2C%20shopping%2C%20and%20travel%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Courtney%20Alev%2C%20a%20consumer%20advocate%20at%20Credit%20Karma.%20%26quot%3BThat%20combined%20with%20the%20fact%20that%20they%20have%20just%20had%20fewer%20earning%20years%20explains%20why%20their%20credit-card%20debt%20is%20growing%20at%20a%20faster%20rate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Gen%20Zers'%20overall%20debt%20levels%20are%20still%20lower%20than%20older%20generations'%2C%20young%20consumers'%20early%20reliance%20on%20credit%20cards%20puts%20their%20financial%20futures%20at%20risk.%20%26quot%3BThe%20financial%20burdens%20that%20Gen%20Z%20is%20facing%20today%20can%20really%20have%20long-lasting%20effects%20on%20their%20lives%2C%26quot%3B%20Alev%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bincluding%20their%20ability%20to%20achieve%20key%20milestones%2C%20such%20as%20delaying%20big%20moments%20like%20marriage%2C%20buying%20a%20home%2C%20or%20starting%20families%20until%20they%20feel%20more%20financially%20secure.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20Gen%20Zers'%20interest%20in%20credit%20cards%20is%20simply%20the%20march%20of%20technological%20progress.%20The%20digital%20natives%20have%20more%20payment%20options%20than%20any%20generation%20before%20them%2C%20and%20they've%20embraced%20electronic%20payments%20and%20alternative%20credit%20methods%20like%20digital%20wallets%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Fbusiness%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbuy-now-pay-later-daily-essentials-groceries-young-adults-rcna141718%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuy-now-pay-later%20apps%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Meanwhile%2C%20credit-card%20companies%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-express-platinum-card-gold-gen-z-millennial-rewards-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etargeted%20young%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20eager%20new%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20some%20acute%20financial%20reasons%20Gen%20Zers%20have%20been%20jumping%20headfirst%20into%20the%20credit%20pool.%20Pandemic%20restrictions%2C%20inflation%2C%20and%20high%20interest%20rates%20hit%20them%20hard%20as%20they%20were%20starting%20their%20professional%20careers%20and%20getting%20their%20financial%20footing.%20As%20young%20people%20sought%20solutions%20to%20financial%20stresses%2C%20and%20as%20credit-card%20balances%20fell%2C%20credit-card%20companies%20were%20more%20than%20willing%20to%20make%20Gen%20Zers%20an%20offer.%20The%20companies%20made%20getting%20credit%20easier%20in%202021%20and%202022%20by%20allowing%20people%20with%20lower%20credit%20scores%20to%20access%20cards%20for%20which%20they%20previously%20would%20have%20been%20ineligible.%20Young%20people%20opened%20credit%20cards%20at%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fgen-z-credit-card-debt-inflation-2f2f927e%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efaster%3C%2Fa%3E%20rate%20than%20any%20other%20age%20group%20during%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20temptation%20to%20use%20those%20cards%20was%20strong.%20Credit%20Karma%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.creditkarma.com%2Finsights%2Fi%2Fstate-of-debt-and-credit-report%23methodology%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3C%2Fa%3Efound%20that%20its%20Gen%20Z%20members'%20average%20credit-card%20debt%20increased%20by%203.2%25%20from%20the%20first%20quarter%20to%20the%20second%20quarter%20of%202024%2C%20while%20the%20average%20debt%20for%20millennials%2C%20Gen%20Xers%2C%20and%20baby%20boomers%20increased%20by%202.4%25%2C%202%25%2C%20and%201.6%25.%20While%20credit-card%20balances%20in%20the%20US%20decreased%20early%20in%20the%20pandemic%2C%20it%20didn't%20take%20long%20for%20American%20consumers%20to%20start%20racking%20up%20debt%20again.%20Credit-card%20balances%20have%20risen%20by%20%24396%20billion%20since%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202021%2C%20a%2051%25%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20people%20accumulated%20credit-card%20debt%20in%20a%20wave%20of%20post-pandemic%20revenge%20spending%3B%20some%20were%20chasing%20points%20and%20rewards.%20Still%20others%20said%20they%20racked%20up%20big%20bills%20because%20they%20couldn't%20afford%20not%20to.%20Regardless%20of%20the%20reasons%2C%20it's%20clear%20that%20many%20Gen%20Zers%20are%20comfortable%20with%20their%20little%20pieces%20of%20plastic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDanikowski%2C%20for%20example%2C%20told%20me%20he%20fell%20into%20the%20credit-card%20trap%20after%20acquiring%20an%20American%20Express%20gold%20travel%20card%20with%20a%20sky-high%20annual%20percentage%20rate.%20The%20card%20let%20him%20build%20up%20points%2C%20which%20allowed%20him%20to%20continue%20traveling.%20%26quot%3BI%20got%20so%20used%20to%20this%20lifestyle%20I%20lived%20for%20the%20last%20three%20years%20that%20it%20became%20hard%20for%20me%20to%20cut%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%2C%20like%20Nico%2C%20a%2027-year-old%20advertising%20strategist%2C%20got%20caught%20in%20a%20post-pandemic%20spending%20cycle.%20After%20graduating%20from%20college%20in%202020%2C%20Nico%20moved%20back%20home%20with%20his%20mom%20to%20save%20money%20while%20working%20remotely.%20By%20late%202021%2C%20Nico%20was%20ready%20for%20a%20change.%20After%20he%20moved%20to%20Chicago%2C%20he%20started%20using%20his%20credit%20card%20way%20more.%20He%20was%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-housing-costs-insurance-debt-election-trump-biden-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20struggling%20to%20make%20his%20%241%2C100%20rent%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20a%20%2436%2C000%20salary.%20In%20addition%20to%20paying%20his%20bills%20and%20making%20sure%20he%20had%20groceries%2C%20Nico%20was%20trying%20to%20make%20new%20friends%20in%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20couldn't%20afford%20to%20live%2C%20but%20I'm%20in%20a%20new%20city%2C%20and%20I%20want%20to%20go%20out%20and%20meet%20people.%20I%20called%20those%20my%20fun%20expenses%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20started%20putting%20all%20of%20that%20on%20my%20credit%20card.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENico%20kept%20reaching%20his%20credit%20limit%2C%20and%20the%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecredit-card%20company%20kept%20extending%20it.%20Three%20years%20later%2C%20he%20has%20about%20%2420%2C000%20in%20credit-card%20debt%20and%20a%20monthly%20minimum%20payment%20of%20%24400%2C%20nearly%20all%20of%20which%20goes%20toward%20interest.%20Landing%20a%20higher-paying%20job%20has%20helped%20him%20start%20to%20get%20a%20handle%20on%20the%20debt%2C%20he%20said.%20He's%20stopped%20using%20the%20card%20and%20tries%20to%20make%20a%20payment%20of%20%24700%20to%20%24900%20each%20month%20in%20hopes%20of%20bringing%20his%20total%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECredit%20proved%20vital%20for%20Emmaline%2C%20a%2027-year-old%20web%20developer%20in%20North%20Carolina%2C%20when%20she%20had%20to%20make%20ends%20meet%20during%20a%20career%20pivot.%20She%20racked%20up%20%246%2C000%20in%20credit-card%20debt%20while%20attending%20a%20full-time%20coding%20boot%20camp%2C%20using%20the%20card%20to%20to%20pay%20for%20groceries%2C%20car%20maintenance%20and%20insurance%2C%20and%20other%20life%20expenses.%20While%20the%20card%20was%20a%20lifeline%20as%20she%20tried%20to%20set%20herself%20up%20for%20a%20successful%20career%2C%20she%20felt%20ashamed%20and%20worried%20about%20her%20debt%2C%20she%20tells%20me.%20For%20a%20long%20time%20she%20kept%20it%20a%20secret.%20This%20year%20she%20finally%20opened%20up%20to%20family%20members%2C%20who%20helped%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-score%2Fhow-to-pay-off-debt-fast%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emake%20a%20plan%20to%20pay%20it%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20offered%20some%20financial%20assistance.%20After%20spending%20a%20few%20months%20throwing%20nearly%20every%20penny%20she%20had%20at%20the%20debt%2C%20Emmaline%20was%20able%20to%20pay%20it%20all%20off%20in%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20made%20sure%20I%20was%20only%20eating%20beans%20and%20leaving%20myself%20money%20for%20gas%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20let%20out%20a%20tear%20or%20two%20of%20pure%20joy%20and%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaid-off-credit-card-debt-solid-plan-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20relief%20when%20it%20was%20finally%20paid%20off%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Zers%20are%20far%20from%20alone%20in%20racking%20up%20credit-card%20debt%3A%20The%20total%20credit-card%20balance%20held%20by%20US%20consumers%20surpassed%20%241%20trillion%20in%202023.%20The%20number%20of%20Americans%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-banks-preparing-loan-loss-credit-card-auto-debt-cre-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estruggling%20to%20pay%20off%20their%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20also%20rising.%20But%20the%20particular%20danger%20for%20Gen%20Zers%20is%20becoming%20so%20reliant%20on%20credit%20cards%20so%20early%20in%20their%20financial%20lives.%20Higher%20debt%2C%20Alev%20says%2C%20can%20lead%20to%20lower%20credit%20scores%20that%20could%20make%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-borrowers-delay-having-kids-buying-car-home-marriage-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20difficult%20to%20pay%20for%20things%20like%20a%20house%20or%20a%20car%3C%2Fa%3E.%20From%20March%202022%20to%20February%202024%2C%20the%20percentage%20of%20Credit%20Karma's%20Gen%20Z%20members%20with%20subprime%20credit%2C%20meaning%20a%20score%20below%20600%2C%20rose%20by%208%20points%2C%20to%2033%25%20from%2025%25%2C%20while%20the%20percentage%20of%20millennials%20with%20subprime%20credit%20scores%20increased%20by%206%20points.%20Credit%20Karma%20said%20the%20average%20Gen%20Z%20credit%20score%20dropped%20to%20659%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%20from%20671%20in%20the%20first%20quarter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilliam%2C%20a%2027-year-old%20emergency%20medical%20technician%20in%20Colorado%2C%20has%20about%20%2420%2C000%20in%20credit-card%20debt%2C%20accumulated%20over%204%20%C2%BD%20years.%20His%20first%20job%20out%20of%20college%20in%202020%20came%20with%20a%20salary%20of%20%2427%2C000.%20Struggling%20to%20get%20by%2C%20William%20primarily%20used%20his%20credit%20card%20for%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-gen-z-splurge-groceries-spending-inflation-gen-z-boomers-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20necessities%20like%20groceries%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20bills%2C%20and%20car%20maintenance.%20But%20when%20a%20health%20emergency%20kept%20him%20out%20of%20work%20for%20weeks%2C%20his%20balance%20snowballed.%20These%20days%2C%20William%20makes%20his%20minimum%20payment%2C%20but%20nearly%20all%20of%20it%20goes%20to%20interest.%20He%20says%20he%20once%20dreamed%20of%20moving%20abroad%20and%20teaching%20English%20but%20has%20accepted%20that%20his%20credit-card%20debt%20keeps%20him%20tethered%20to%20a%20reliable%20source%20of%20income%20stateside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'd%20like%20to%20have%20a%20family%20one%20day%20and%20be%20able%20to%20settle%20down%20and%20raise%20kids%2C%20give%20them%20a%20good%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20William%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20that's%20not%20something%20I%20can%20do%20until%20I%20have%20a%20better%20hold%20on%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20clear%20that%20Gen%20Zers'%20habits%20will%20change%20anytime%20soon.%20The%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20New%20York%20said%20in%20August%20that%20younger%20debt-holders%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20delinquent%20on%20their%20credit-card%20payments%20than%20older%20ones.%20Falling%20behind%20on%20these%20payments%20has%20given%20young%20people%20a%20bleak%20outlook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCredit-card%20debt%20is%20an%20invisible%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20Emmaline%20says.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20see%20it.%20It%20veils%20you%20in%20shame.%20It%20eats%20you%20like%20a%20parasite.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlev%20says%20there%20are%20some%20steps%20people%20can%20take%20to%20try%20to%20escape%20credit%20debt.%20First%20and%20foremost%2C%20she%20cautions%20people%20to%20stay%20as%20far%20away%20from%20high-interest%20debt%20as%20possible.%20She%20also%20advises%20debt-holders%20to%20stop%20using%20that%20credit%20line%20and%20make%20a%20plan%20to%20pay%20down%20the%20debt%2C%20such%20as%20transferring%20the%20debt%20to%20a%20personal%20loan%20at%20a%20lower%20interest%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20important%2C%20she%20says%2C%20members%20of%20the%20credit-card%20generation%20shouldn't%20bury%20their%20heads%20in%20the%20sand.%20She%20recommends%20people%20create%20a%20spreadsheet%20listing%20all%20their%20debts%20along%20with%20minimum%20payments%2C%20interest%20rates%2C%20and%20consolidation%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20William%20feels%20suffocated%20by%20his%20monthly%20payments%20and%20interest%20rate%2C%20he%20can%20feel%20tempted%20to%20rack%20up%20even%20more%20debt.%20%26quot%3BSomeone%20is%20always%20willing%20to%20give%20you%20another%20credit%20card%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDanikowski%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20said%20feeling%20hopeless%20about%20his%20debt%20was%20pointless.%20Though%20he%20lost%20his%20job%20this%20year%2C%20he%20still%20took%20trips%20to%20Europe%20and%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20know%20it's%20not%20a%20good%20decision%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20at%20least%20I've%20gotten%20to%20see%20the%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Ferin-snodgrass%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EErin%20Snodgrass%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3Eis%20a%20senior%20reporter%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgeneration-credit-card-gen-z-high-levels-debt-spending-points-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733303042000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6716c5049b3250dbbce90820%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgeneration-credit-card-gen-z-high-levels-debt-spending-points-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Gen%20Z%20is%20more%20comfortable%20with%20credit%20cards%20than%20any%20previous%20generation.%20But%20the%20reliance%20on%20debt%20could%20come%20back%20to%20bite%20them.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22esnodgrass%40businessinsider.com%20(Erin%20Snodgrass)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgeneration-credit-card-gen-z-high-levels-debt-spending-points-2024-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20most%20common%20jobs%20for%20US%20men%20and%20women%20without%20college%20degrees%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224982%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Construction%20workers%20in%20a%20construction%20site.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%