o%20the%20end%20of%20World%20War%20II%20in%201945%20when%20global%20powers%20divided%20the%20region%20into%20two%20zones.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20the%20split%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnAfter%20Japan's%20defeat%20in%20World%20War%20II%2C%20Korea%2C%20previously%20under%20Japanese%20control%2C%20faced%20an%20uncertain%20future.%20The%20US%20and%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20stepped%20in%2C%20dividing%20Korea%20along%20the%2038th%20parallel.%20The%20Soviet%20Union%20occupied%20the%20North%2C%20while%20the%20US%20controlled%20the%20South.%20This%20division%20happened%20without%20consulting%20Koreans.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnAttempts%20to%20reunify%20Korea%20failed%20as%20the%20Cold%20War%20deepened.%20The%20Soviets%20and%20Americans%20refused%20to%20relinquish%20control%2C%20preventing%20negotiations%20for%20a%20middle%20ground.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnIn%20the%20North%2C%20the%20Soviets%20supported%20a%20communist%20government%20under%20Kim%20Il-sung%20while%20the%20US%20backed%20an%20anti-communist%20regime%20led%20by%20Syngman%20Rhee%20in%20the%20South.%20In%201948%2C%20South%20Korea%20officially%20formed%20a%20government%20in%20Seoul%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20North%20declaring%20its%20own%20state%20in%20Pyongyang.%20Both%20claimed%20to%20represent%20all%20of%20Korea.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Korean%20war%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnTensions%20erupted%20into%20the%20Korean%20War%20in%201950%20when%20North%20Korea%2C%20backed%20by%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20and%20China%2C%20invaded%20the%20South.%20The%20US%20intervened%2C%20urging%20its%20member%20states%20to%20send%20military%20aid%20to%20South%20Korea.%20The%20US%2C%20Great%20Britain%2C%20Australia%2C%20and%20Canada%20joined%20the%20efforts%2C%20contributing%20troops%20to%20counter%20the%20invasion.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnPeace%20negotiators%20began%20talks%20in%20July%201951%2C%20but%20progress%20remained%20slow.%20For%20two%20years%2C%20opposing%20forces%20fought%20intensely%20while%20diplomatic%20efforts%20continued.%20On%20July%2027%2C%201953%2C%20representatives%20from%20the%20US%2C%20China%2C%20North%20Korea%2C%20and%20South%20Korea%20signed%20an%20armistice%20(not%20a%20peace%20treaty)%20at%20Panmunjom.%20This%20agreement%20ended%20active%20hostilities%20but%20maintained%20Korea's%20division.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20Demilitarised%20Zone%20(DMZ)%20was%20established%20along%20the%2038th%20parallel%2C%20creating%20one%20of%20the%20most%20heavily%20fortified%20borders%20in%20the%20world.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnOften%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BForgotten%20War%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Korean%20conflict%20left%20a%20devastating%20toll.%20It%20killed%20over%20three%20million%20and%20displaced%20countless%20people%2C%20making%20it%20one%20of%20the%20most%20tragic%20episodes%20of%20the%20Cold%20War%20era.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20keeps%20them%20apart%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnSince%20the%20split%2C%20North%20Korea%20has%20remained%20an%20isolated%20communist%20regime%20under%20the%20Kim%20dynasty%2C%20focusing%20on%20military%20strength%20and%20nuclear%20weapons.%20South%20Korea%2C%20on%20the%20contrary%2C%20developed%20into%20a%20democratic%2C%20economically%20advanced%20nation%20with%20strong%20ties%20to%20the%20West.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnEfforts%20at%20reunification%2C%20including%20talks%20and%20summits%2C%20have%20made%20little%20progress.%20The%20ideological%20divide%20and%20mutual%20mistrust%20have%20kept%20the%20two%20Koreas%20apart%2C%20with%20tensions%20occasionally%20escalating%20due%20to%20military%20provocations%20from%20the%20North.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733299440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2F4rmu7pt8_north-korea_625x300_15_August_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fthe-north-south-divide-explained-how-korea-became-two-nations-7168618%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20Japan's%20defeat%20in%20