202024.%20The%20recognition%20celebrates%20her%20dedication%20to%20championing%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20marginalised%2C%20promoting%20government%20transparency%20and%20empowering%20grassroots%20communities%20across%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20career%20spanning%20over%20four%20decades%20has%20seen%20Ms%20Roy%20work%20for%20social%20justice%20in%20India%20through%20people-led%20initiatives%2C%20cementing%20her%20legacy%20as%20one%20of%20the%20country's%20most%20prominent%20activists.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EEarly%20life%20and%20career%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnBorn%20on%20May%2026%2C%201946%2C%20in%20Madras%20(now%20Chennai)%2C%20Aruna%20Roy%20earned%20a%20postgraduate%20degree%20in%20English%20literature%20from%20Indraprastha%20College%2C%20Delhi%20University.%20She%20began%20her%20professional%20journey%20as%20a%20lecturer%20at%20the%20same%20college%20before%20entering%20the%20IAS%20in%201968.%20But%20her%20aspirations%20extended%20beyond%20bureaucratic%20confines.%20In%201974%2C%20she%20left%20the%20IAS%2C%20driven%20by%20a%20desire%20to%20work%20directly%20with%20rural%20communities%20and%20address%20systemic%20issues%20affecting%20the%20underprivileged.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnShe%20joined%20the%20Social%20Work%20and%20Research%20Centre%20in%20Tilonia%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20an%20organisation%20founded%20by%20her%20husband%2C%20where%20she%20began%20working%20on%20rural%20development%20initiatives.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EBirth%20of%20MKSS%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnIn%201990%2C%20Ms%C2%A0Roy%2C%20along%20with%20a%20few%20others%20from%20the%20Devdungri%20district%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20co-founded%20the%20Mazdoor%20Kisan%20Shakti%20Sangathan%20(MKSS).%20The%20grassroots%20organisation%20aimed%20to%20empower%20workers%20and%20farmers%20by%20advocating%20for%20fair%20wages%2C%20government%20accountability%20and%20transparency.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20MKSS%20gained%20prominence%20in%20the%20campaign%20for%20public%20access%20to%20information%2C%20laying%20the%20groundwork%20for%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20(RTI)%20movement%20in%20India.%20Through%20public%20hearings%2C%20they%20exposed%20corruption%20in%20local%20governance%20and%20mobilised%20public%20support.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3ERight%20to%20Information%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnMs%20Roy's%20efforts%20culminated%20in%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20landmark%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%20in%202005.%20The%20RTI%20Act%20became%20the%20first%20national%20legislation%20born%20out%20of%20a%20people's%20campaign%2C%20with%20MKSS%20leading%20it%20from%20conceptualisation%20to%20drafting%20and%20eventual%20enactment.%20Today%2C%20millions%20of%20Indians%20file%20RTI%20applications%20annually%2C%20holding%20authorities%20accountable%20and%20seeking%20justice.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnAs%20a%20member%20of%20India's%20National%20Advisory%20Council%20from%202004%20to%202006%20and%20again%20from%202010%20to%202013%2C%20Ms%20Roy%20helped%20shape%20other%20legislations%2C%20including%20the%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20National%20Rural%20Employment%20Guarantee%20Act%20(MGNREGA).%20This%20law%20provides%20rural%20households%20with%20a%20legal%20guarantee%20of%20employment%2C%20furthering%20economic%20security%20and%20social%20equity.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EAwards%20and%20recognition%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnAruna%20Roy's%20contributions%20to%20social%20justice%20have%20earned%20her%20numerous%20accolades.%20She%20received%20the%20prestigious%20Ramon%20Magsaysay%20Award%20in%202000%20for%20Community%20Leadership%2C%20often%20called%20Asia's%20Nobel%20Prize.%20In%202011%2C%20she%20was%20named%20among%20TIME%20magazine's%20100%20Most%20Influential%20People%20in%20the%20World.%20Other%20honours%20include%20the%20Nani%20Palkhivala%20Award%20and%20the%20Lal%20Bahadur%20Shastri%20National%20Award%20for%20Excellence%20in%20Public%20Administration%2C%20Academia%2C%20and%20Management%20in%202010.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnMs%20Roy%20continues%20her%20activism%20as%20the%20president%20of%20the%20National%20Federation%20of%20Indian%20Women%20(NFIW).%20In%202024%2C%20she%20published%20her%20memoir%2C%20The%20Personal%20is%20Political%2C%20reflecting%20on%20her%20journey.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733293320000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fq5nafk38_aruna-roy_625x300_04_December_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Faruna-roy-indian-activist-on-bbcs-100-women-of-the-year-2024-list-7167969%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Aruna%20Roy%20is%20an%20Indian%20social%20activist%20and%20co-founder%20of%20the%20Mazdoor%20Kisan%20Shakti%20Sangathan.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Faruna-roy-indian-activist-on-bbcs-100-women-of-the-year-2024-list-7167969%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hrithik%20Roshan%20and%20His%20Family%20to%20Feature%20in%20Netflix%20Documentary%20Series%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733293237000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FThe-Roshans.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236234517%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Netflix%20has%20revealed%20that%20it%20will%20stream%20a%20documentary%20series%20chronicling%20three%20generations%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Roshan%20family%20and%20their%20contributions%20to%20Hindi-language%20cinema.%20The%20series%20marks%20the%20first%20time%20the%20family%20has%20offered%20an%20in-depth%20look%20at%20their%20entertainment%20dynasty.%20The%20documentary%20traces%20the%20family%E2%80%99s%20journey%20from%20patriarch%20Roshan%20Lal%20Nagrath%20(known%20professionally%20as%20Roshan)%2C%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Sahasranaman%20Ramachandran%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2