22author%22%3A%22agoh%40businessinsider.com%20(Amanda%20Goh)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhoda-kotb-former-boss-body-shamed-her-at-work-harassment-2024-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20Judge%20Who%20Rejected%20Elon%20Musk's%20Tesla%20Payday%20Faces%20Backlash%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20social%20media%20blowback%20for%20Delaware%20Judge%20Kathaleen%20St.%20J.%20McCormick%20came%20fast%20and%20furious%20after%20she%20blocked%20Elon%20Musk's%20multibillion-dollar%20Tesla%20Inc.%20payday%20for%20a%20second%20time%2C%20spotlighting%20the%20pressure%20that%20comes%20with%20ruling%20against%20the%20world's%20richest%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMusk%20posted%20%26quot%3Babsolute%20corruption%26quot%3B%20on%20X%20shortly%20after%20the%20ruling%20late%20Monday%20and%20Tesla%20bull%20Cathie%20Wood%20railed%20against%20an%20%26quot%3Bactivist%20judge%20at%20its%20worst%26quot%3B%20who%20she%20accused%20of%20undermining%20the%20rights%20of%20shareholders.%20Other%20backers%20of%20the%20billionaire%20dubbed%20McCormick's%20decision%20%26quot%3Binsane.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMcCormick%2C%20the%20Delaware%20Chancery%20Court's%20chief%20judge%2C%20is%20an%20old%20hand%20at%20dealing%20with%20Musk-related%20backlash.%20In%20January%20she%20got%20an%20earful%20from%20critics%2C%20both%20in%20online%20posts%20and%20letters%20to%20her%20chambers%2C%20when%20she%20first%20voided%20Musk's%20pay%20package%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20Tesla's%20board%20was%20too%20beholden%20to%20him.%20Likewise%20back%20in%202022%20when%20McCormick%20refused%20to%20let%20Musk%20back%20out%20of%20a%20%2444%20billion%20deal%20to%20buy%20X's%20predecessor%2C%20Twitter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Amped%20Up'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20judges%20routinely%20decide%20thorny%20legal%20issues%2C%20those%20determinations%20get%20more%20complicated%20when%20they%20involve%20the%20richest%20and%20most%20powerful%20personalities%20in%20the%20corporate%20world%2C%20said%20Eric%20Talley%2C%20a%20Columbia%20University%20law%20professor%20who%20focuses%20on%20corporate%20litigation.%20%26quot%3BThose%20kinds%20of%20cases%20are%20particularly%20amped-up%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMcCormick%20and%20Musk%20didn't%20respond%20Tuesday%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMusk's%20influence%20has%20reached%20new%20heights%20and%20his%20net%20worth%20has%20soared%20since%20the%20US%20presidential%20election%20because%20he's%20considered%20a%20close%20confidant%20of%20Donald%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20stock%20options%20package%20was%20initially%20worth%20%242.6%20billion%20and%20spiked%20to%20%2456%20billion%20by%20the%20time%20the%20judge%20canceled%20it%20in%20January.%20The%20package%20was%20worth%20%24101.5%20billion%20at%20Monday's%20closing%20price.%20Tesla%20shares%20fell%201.6%25%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20206%20million%20followers%20on%20X%2C%20Musk%20regularly%20relies%20on%20his%20internet%20megaphone%20to%20whip%20up%20his%20fans%2C%20including%20legions%20of%20Tesla%20retail%20investors%2C%20into%20a%20frenzy.%20Scores%20of%20X%20users%2C%20including%20many%20who%20use%20anonymous%20handles%2C%20aimed%20their%20anger%20at%20McCormick%20for%20denying%20Musk%20the%20largest-ever%20pay%20package%20awarded%20to%20a%20corporate%20executive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'In%20Jail'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20needs%20to%20be%20in%20jail%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20user%20named%20Not%20Jerome%20Powell%20wrote%20in%20a%20post%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20judge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMusk%20has%20warned%20that%20McCormick's%20ruling%20will%20prompt%20a%20business%20exodus%20from%20Delaware%2C%20the%20corporate%20home%20to%20about%20two-thirds%20of%20Fortune%20500%20companies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20serial%20entrepreneur%20has%20moved%20to%20incorporate%20Tesla%2C%20his%20rocket%20company%20SpaceX%20and%20other%20businesses%20in%20Texas%2C%20where%20he%20hopes%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20more%20lax%20regulations%20and%20a%20new%20business-court%20system.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20McCormick%20is%20taking%20heat%20for%20her%20ruling%2C%20she's%20also%20reaping%20praise%20from%20some%20legal%20commentators%20for%20not%20bowing%20in%20the%20face%20of%20pressure%20over%20her%20conclusion%20that%20Tesla's%20board%20was%20too%20rife%20with%20conflicts%20of%20interest%20to%20properly%20decide%20Musk's%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECourage%2C%20Integrity%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20rulings%20concerning%20Musk%2C%20she%20has%20%26quot%3Bshown%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20courage%20and%20the%20integrity%20not%20to%20back%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jill%20Fisch%2C%20a%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%20law%20school%20professor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnn%20Lipton%2C%20a%20corporate%20law%20professor%20at%20Tulane%20University%2C%20said%20that%20McCormick's%20ruling%20was%20in%20line%20with%20Delaware%20law%20and%20reinforced%20the%20idea%20that%20Musk%20must%20be%20treated%20just%20like%20other%20corporate%20bosses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20of%20Musk's%20supporters%20and%20admirers%20believe%20corporate%20managers%20like%20him%20shouldn't%20be%20restrained%2C%26quot%3B%20Lipton%20said.%20Being%20the%20first%20woman%20chief%20judge%20in%20Chancery%20also%20makes%20McCormick%20a%20high-profile%20target%2C%20she%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWedbush%20analyst%20Daniel%20Ives%20said%20in%20a%20note%20to%20investors%20that%20McCormick's%20ruling%20wasn't%20a%20surprise%20and%20may%20not%20be%20the%20final%20word%20on%20Musk's%20pay.%20Tesla%20has%20already%20said%20it%20plans%20to%20appeal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20continues%20to%20be%20a%20soap%20opera%20playing%20out%20in%20Delaware.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20is%20Tornetta%20v.%